ted lightlike solitons is\nconsidered. The representation of arbitrary polarization for the beam with the\ntwisted lightlike solitons is discussed. It is shown that the effect of\nmechanical angular momentum transfer to absorbent by the circularly polarized\nbeam can be provided. This effect is well known for photon beam. Thus the\nsoliton solution which have determinate likeness with photon is obtained in\nparticular.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 30 Jun 2015 16:07:54 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 13 Jul 2015 18:16:59 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 21 Jul 2015 06:24:02 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 4 Aug 2015 19:22:38 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Thu, 22 Oct 2015 18:52:50 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Fri, 17 Jun 2016 12:18:11 GMT"},{"version":"v7","created":"Tue, 20 Mar 2018 20:01:07 GMT"},{"version":"v8","created":"Sat, 5 Jan 2019 12:56:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-01-08"}
